title: Zelensky to Meet With Biden in Washington Next Week
description: The Ukrainian leader will go from an appearance at the United Nations General Assembly to the capital to meet with President Biden and members of Congress.

title: Report of Spyware Attack on a Russian Journalist Raises Concern Among Others
description: Apple has sent notifications to at least several more Russian reporters and editors that their cellphones might be under “state-sponsored” attacks.

title: U.S. Approves $235 Million in Egypt Aid, Choosing Security Over Rights
description: Secretary of State Antony J. Blinken overruled congressional restrictions on U.S. military aid tied to Egypt’s dismal human rights record.

title: Dominican Republic Will Close Border With Haiti Amid Water Dispute
description: The Dominican president said the military would enforce the measure on Friday morning. Experts warned the closure could deepen Haiti’s economic crisis.

title: Friday Briefing: A Call for Answers in Libya
description: Plus an Afghan soccer captain fighting for girls.

title: U.S. Aims New Sanctions at Russian Military Supply Chains
description: The sanctions are intended to deprive President Vladimir V. Putin of equipment and technology “he needs to wage his barbaric war on Ukraine,” Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen said.

title: C.I.A. Discloses Identity of Second Spy Involved in ‘Argo’ Operation
description: The movie about the daring mission to rescue American diplomats from Tehran portrayed a single C.I.A. officer sneaking into the Iranian capital. In reality, the agency sent two officers.

title: Hugo Blanco, Environmental Activist in Peru and Beyond, Dies at 88
description: He argued that global capitalism was at the root of the global ecological crisis, and he spent decades fighting for an alternative.

title: Ukraine Intensifies Attacks on Russia in Crimea and Black Sea
description: Claims of damage to Russian air defenses and warships reflect Ukraine’s growing strategy of degrading the Kremlin’s ability to use the region as a staging area that is vital to its war effort.

title: Biden Taps Penny Pritzker to Drive Ukraine’s Economic Revival
description: The appointment of the former commerce secretary and Democratic Party fund-raiser reflects a growing focus on Ukraine’s postwar economic survival.

title: Senate Committee Backs Bill to Deepen U.S. Economic Ties With Taiwan
description: Legislation to end double taxation between Taiwan and the United States is intended to spur semiconductor investment but is likely to rankle U.S. relations with China.

title: Venice Keeps Off UNESCO World Heritage Danger List
description: The fragile Italian city has taken steps to reduce the impacts of climate change and excessive tourism, but some experts said the moves were not enough.

title: Éva Fahidi, Outspoken Holocaust Survivor, Dies at 97
description: She saw her family members marched off to their deaths while she went to a forced-labor camp. It took her almost 60 years to begin telling her story.

title: Spain’s Female Soccer Players Call Off Wage Dispute Strike
description: The breakthrough in the labor dispute, which has delayed the start of the season and has added to a turbulent period in Spanish soccer, was an agreement over minimum pay.

title: Gridlock, Confusion and Waiting: On the Road With Spanish Rescuers in Morocco
description: Our video journalists embedded with a team of Spanish military rescuers in Morocco as they attempted to save lives after the earthquake. They spent much of the day waiting for orders.

title: A Family Who Survived Morocco’s Earthquake Feel Blessed By New Life
description: Clambering away from an earthquake’s devastation and death, a family emerges treasuring a single new life.

title: Russia-Ukraine War : Russia Thwarts Attack in Crimea a Day After Ukraine Struck Two Naval Ships
description: Ukraine appeared to target another Russian boat docked in the Black Sea, home to a fleet of Russian ships.

title: Amid Rescue Efforts After Libya Floods, a Call for Accountability
description: The government of one side of the country has called for an investigation into how two dams collapsed and into reports that aid had been hindered.

title: Politicians Charge Millions to Send Migrants to U.S. Through Darién Gap
description: The Biden administration vowed to “end the illicit movement” of people through the Darién jungle. But the number of migrants moving through the forest has never been greater — and the profits are too big to pass up.

title: LVMH’s Bernard Arnault Is the King of Luxury, but Who Is Next to the Throne?
description: With brands like Tiffany, Dom Pérignon and Louis Vuitton, LVMH turned him into one of the world’s richest men. But with five children, he has a hard decision to make.

title: A Luxury Cruise Ship Is Stuck Off Greenland’s Coast
description: The Ocean Explorer had been traveling toward Northeast Greenland National Park when it ran aground on Monday, officials said. The ship is still stuck.

title: China Conducts Major Military Exercises in Western Pacific
description: The drills, which appear to simulate a blockade of Taiwan, are believed to be in response to recent military drills between the United States and allies.

title: Now the Koreas Are Selling Weapons to the West
description: Desperate for munitions for the war in Ukraine, the U.S. and Russia have turned to their allies in South and North Korea, which kept stockpiling arms for decades after their own conflict.

title: Thursday Briefing
description: Catastrophic flooding in Libya.

title: Tiny Homes Are a Social Media Hit. But Do We Want to Live in Them?
description: Social media platforms are awash with videos of microapartments and tiny homes, amassing tens of millions of views. But do clicks translate into new occupants?

title: Ufologist Claims to Show Mummified Alien Specimens to Mexico's Congress
description: In a jaw-dropping presentation, a self-proclaimed ufologist showed members of Congress what he claimed were two mummified specimens of extraterrestrial beings.
